-- Lazard Is Advising Abertis's Owners on Possible Buyout, Il Messaggero Says
-- Elisa Martinuzzi
-- 2010-07-06T07:35:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/lazard-is-advising-abertis-s-owners-on-possible-buyout-il-messaggero-says.html

          
          
             Lazard Ltd. is advising shareholders
of Abertis Infraestucturas SA on a buyout of the company,  Il
Messaggero  reported, without saying how it obtained the
information.  
 Mediobanca SpA has lined up 10 banks that will lend 600
million euros ($755 million) each to fund the purchase, the
daily newspaper reported today. Among the lenders are Credit
Agricole SA, BNP Paribas SA, Societe Generale SA, Intesa
Sanpaolo SpA, UniCredit SpA, Banco Santander SA and Banco Bilbao
Vizcaya Argentaria SA, the newspaper said.  
          
          


  


        